# Backend Configuration – ChromaDB Client

This document explains how the **backend service connects to the Chroma vector database** created by the ingestion pipeline.

The backend reads embeddings stored in ChromaDB and uses them for **Retrieval Augmented Generation (RAG)** when answering user questions.

---

# Project Structure

```text id="q7h9f3"
project/
│
├─ ingestion/
│   ├─ ingest_api.py
│   ├─ chroma_client.py
│   └─ chroma-data/        # Chroma database stored here
│
├─ backend/
│   ├─ rag_api.py
│   ├─ chroma_client.py
│   └─ .env
│
└─ requirements.txt
```

The ingestion pipeline stores vector embeddings inside:

```id="ewi6q9"
ingestion/chroma-data/
```

The backend connects to the **same database folder** to retrieve document embeddings.

